1. Register Borrower (POST /api/borrowers)
Description: Adds a new borrower to the system.


curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/borrowers \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
-d '{
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "name": "John Doe"
}'
---------------------------------------------------------

2. Get All Borrowers (GET /api/borrowers)
Description: Retrieves a list of all borrowers.

curl -X GET http://localhost:8080/api/borrowers \
-H "Accept: application/json"

----------------------------------------------------------

3. Get Borrower Details (GET /api/borrowers/{id})
Description: Retrieves details of a specific borrower by their ID.

curl -X GET http://localhost:8080/api/borrowers/1 \
-H "Accept: application/json"

----------------------------------------------------------

4. Register Book (POST /api/books)
Description: Adds a new book to the system.

curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/books \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
-d '{
  "isbn": "978-3-16-148410-0",
  "title": "Effective Java",
  "author": "Joshua Bloch",
  "borrowerId": 1
}'

------------------------------------------------------------

5. Get All Books (GET /api/books)
Description: Retrieves a list of all books.

curl -X GET http://localhost:8080/api/books \
-H "Accept: application/json"

--------------------------------------------------------------

6. Get Book Details (GET /api/books/{id})
Description: Retrieves details of a specific book by its ID.

curl -X GET http://localhost:8080/api/books/1 \
-H "Accept: application/json"

------------------------------------------------------------

7. Borrow a Book (POST /api/borrowers/{borrowerId}/borrow/{bookId})
Description: Assigns a book to a borrower.

curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/borrowers/1/borrow/1 \
-H "Accept: application/json"

-----------------------------------------------------------

8. Return a Book (POST /api/borrowers/{borrowerId}/return/{bookId})
Description: Removes a book assignment from a borrower.

curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/borrowers/1/return/1 \
-H "Accept: application/json"






